    {
      "letter": "b",
      "prompt": "Let $y = f(x)$ be the particular solution to the given differential equation with the initial condition $f(2) = 3$. Write an equation for the line tangent to the graph of $y = f(x)$ at $x = 2$. Use your equation to approximate $f(2.1)$.",
      "point_value": 2,
      "scoring_notes": "From scoring key: Slope at $(2, 3)$ is $\\frac{3^2}{2-1} = 9$. Tangent line: $y = 3 + 9(x-2)$. Approximation: $f(2.1) \\approx 3.9$.",
