    {
      "letter": "c",
      "prompt": "Find the particular solution $y = f(x)$ to the given differential equation with the initial condition $f(2) = 3$.",
      "point_value": 5,
      "scoring_notes": "From scoring key: $-\\frac{1}{y} = \\ln|x-1| + C$. Using $f(2)=3$: $C = -\\frac{1}{3}$. Final answer: $y = f(x) = \\frac{1}{\\frac{1}{3} - \\ln(x-1)}$, valid for $1 < x < 1 + e^{1/3}$. 0/5 if no separation; max 3/5 if no constant of integration.",
